  "market_context": "Bitcoin was trading in a defined daily range with clear support and resistance. Price formed successive higher lows as it approached the upper resistance boundary, increasing probability of an upside breakout.",
  "key_observation": "Before the upside breakout, price printed one low, then a higher low, then another higher low—indicating strengthening bullish momentum into resistance.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst applied the LuxAlgo Range Detector indicator to automatically identify the trading range (support at ~28500–30000, resistance at ~31000 on earlier frames; later range shifted higher).",
    "Step 2: The analyst observed that price formed three sequential higher lows as it approached the upper resistance level of the range.",
    "Step 3: The analyst noted that this pattern of higher lows into resistance increases the likelihood of a successful upside breakout, per prior teaching in the video.",
    "Step 4: The analyst confirmed the breakout when the Range Detector’s horizontal line turned green, signaling an upside break of the established range."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Higher lows approaching resistance act as a confluence signal for breakout trades; combining range detection with price structure (higher lows) improves breakout reliability without relying on lagging indicators.",
